Two persons were allegedly abducted on Monday along old Ibadan-Iwo road, Osun State by suspected kidnappers, TribuneOnline authoritatively gathered. The abducted persons, whose identities remain unknown as of the time of filing this report were among the passengers travelling along the axis before they were attacked by gunmen. Credible security source informed our correspondent that the abduction occurred around 11.15 pm on Monday night around Alamo village. Lawyer, son docked for alleged N1m fraud in Osun Police kill two suspected armed robbers in Anambra Man dies after allegedly drinking herbal mixture in Osun Police arrested 275 suspected criminals in Kwara in 2019’ ALSO READ: Meeting with Buhari: ASUU demands declaration of 5-year state of emergency on education Though details surrounding their abduction were still sketchy, efforts were already on by security agencies to rescue them When contacted, the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) of Osun State Police command, Mrs Folasade Odoro confirmed the incident, saying rescue operation had been launched by the Police to secure the freedom for the abductees. According to her, “the Commissioner of Police in Osun, Mr Babatunde Kokumo had already visited the scene of the incident and our men are presently combing the bush to rescue the kidnapped individuals unhurt.” STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO  WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS FREE